The paper focuses on developing a deep architecture for learning aesthetically-relevant visual attributes from Flickr images, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image retargeting, aesthetics ranking, and retrieval. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a bag-of-words (BoW) representation and a sparsity-constrained subspace algorithm, which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and multimedia (MM) research. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is the second most likely sub-category. The paper also involves weakly-supervised learning algorithms, which are a subset of machine learning (ML) techniques, and the use of a convolutional neural network (CNN), which is a popular deep learning (DL) technique. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions psychological and anatomical studies related to human perception, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (HCI). Hence, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible sub-category.
